description:
&lt;p&gt;Ward 10 is an Emergency Surgical ward for patients who need surgery or treatment for surgical emergencies. The Ward admits patients with Urology , Lower Gastrointestinal and Upper Gastro intestinal surgery. You will gain experience nursing patients who have had major bowel surgery, patients with galls stones, kidney stones, urinary retention and haematuria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would support you by giving you a 4 week supernumerary period with buddy to actively develop your knowledge and skills and can offer as well as a Ward based induction to teach you the necessary skills and a full trust induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, hard-working, motivated individuals to work within the team on the Surgical Ward to provide excellent care with compassion.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants will already possess strong communication skills and will need to demonstrate excellent infection control standards. You will be expected to carry out all levels of patient care relevant to the band 3 role. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for individuals who are keen to learn new skills, enjoy a challenge and have a commitment to the health and wellbeing of the people we care for. Recent experience of working at a Band 2/3 level in an acute setting is essential. Training within this specialty will be provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*** GCSE&#39;s in Maths and English Grade C or above (or equivalent) and an NVQ in Health level 3 is essential in order to apply for this position. ***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
